ssions, packet loss, and network interface errors to more quickly isolate the source of network degradation. 2. Investigate the cause of the CPU pressure on os_018 to ensure nodes have sufficient resources to handle both application logic and network I/O. 3. Configure alerting on critical network health indicators such as \'Received_errors_packets\' and sustained \'Received_queue\' growth to enable proactive response.\n\nBackgroud:\n"\n\n\nBased on this information, identify the MOST LIKELY root cause component and reason from the candidate list.\nFollow these rules:\n- The root cause must be a single component from the candidate list.\n- The reason must be directly supported by the anomaly description.\n- Assign a suspicious score between 0.0 and 1.0 (higher = more confident).\n\nRespond ONLY with a JSON object in this exact format:\n{\n    "component": "service-name",\n    "reason": "brief reason",\n    "score": 0.92\n}'}]
